# Experimental image data is kept OUT of the repository by default.
#
# Reasons: this repo is public, SMLM stacks routinely exceed GitHub's 100 MB
# per-file hard limit, and anything committed stays in git history forever
# (bloating every future clone) even if deleted later.
#
# Files here are still fully usable locally for benchmarking — they just are
# not tracked. To deliberately commit a small fixture, force-add it:
#     git add -f experimental_data/small_crop.tif

*.tif
*.tiff
*.nd2
*.czi
*.lif
*.ome.tif
*.ome.tiff
*.csv
*.zip

# ...but keep this folder's own documentation tracked
!.gitignore
!README.md
